nalysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a>   <span class=\"fn\">C</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.MeasureSpace.volume\">MeasureTheory.volume</a>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.Measure.real\">real</a></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#setOf\">{</a><span class=\"fn\">t</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#setOf\">:</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#setOf\">|</a> <span class=\"fn\">t</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Interval/Set/Defs.html#Set.Ioo\">Set.Ioo</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <span class=\"fn\">1</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/LineDeriv/Basic.html#lineDeriv\">lineDeriv</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/AffineMap.html#AffineMap.lineMap\">AffineMap.lineMap</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">t</span>)</span> (<span class=\"fn\">b</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span>)</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Ne\">≠</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#setOf\">}</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Consider a function `f : E → F` continuous on a segment `[a, b]`\nand line differentiable in the direction `b - a` at all points of the open segment `(a, b)`.\n\nIf `‖∂_{b - a} f‖ ≤ C` at a.e. all points of the open segment,\nthen `‖f b - f a‖ ≤ C * volume s`, where `s` is the set of points `t ∈ Ioo 0 1`\nsuch that `f` has nonzero line derivative in the direction `b - a` at `lineMap a b t`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/IntervalIntegral/DistLEIntegral.html#norm_sub_le_mul_volume_of_norm_lineDeriv_le","kind":"theorem","line":118,"name":"norm_sub_le_mul_volume_of_norm_lineDeriv_le","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/IntervalIntegral/DistLEIntegral.lean#L118-L145"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/IntervalIntegral/DistLEIntegral.html#norm_sub_le_mul_volume_of_norm_deriv_le_of_le\"><span class=\"name\">norm_sub_le_mul_volume_of_norm_deriv_le_of_le</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#NormedAddCommGroup\">NormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Basic.html#NormedSpace\">NormedSpace</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> → <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>}</span></s