→ <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/Deriv/Basic.html#deriv\">deriv</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">t</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">B</span> <span class=\"fn\">t</span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hBi</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/IntervalIntegral/Basic.html#IntervalIntegrable\">IntervalIntegrable</a> <span class=\"fn\">B</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.MeasureSpace.volume\">MeasureTheory.volume</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/IntervalIntegral/Basic.html#intervalIntegral\">∫</a> (<span class=\"fn\">t</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>) <a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/IntervalIntegral/Basic.html#intervalIntegral\">in</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/IntervalIntegral/Basic.html#intervalIntegral\">..</a><span class=\"fn\">b</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/IntervalIntegral/Basic.html#intervalIntegral\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">B</span> <span class=\"fn\">t</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Displacement is at most the integral of an upper estimate on the speed.\n\nLet `f : ℝ → E` be a function which is continuous on a closed interval `[a, b]`\nand is differentiable on the open interval `(a, b)`.\nIf `B t` is an integrable upper estimate on `‖f' t‖`, `a < t < b`,\nthen `‖f b - f a‖ ≤ ∫ t in a..b, B t`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/IntervalIntegral/DistLEIntegral.html#norm_sub_le_integral_of_norm_deriv_le_of_le","kind":"theorem","line":37,"name":"norm_sub_le_integral_of_norm_deriv_le_of_le","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/IntervalIntegral/DistLEIntegral.lean#L37-L79"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Analysis.Calculus.Deriv.Basic","Mathlib.Analysis.Calculus.DiffContOnCl","Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Integral.IntervalIntegral.Basic","Mathlib.Analysis.Calculus.LineDeriv.Basic","Mathlib.Analysis.Calculus.MeanValue","Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Integral.IntervalIntegral.FundThmCalculus","Mathlib.Analysis.Normed.Module.Completion"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Integral.IntervalIntegral.DistLEIntegral"}